{
  "doc_id": "6015",
  "text": "Finally, several works closely derived from the machine learning-based score analysis work of [CITATION_1] can also be found in the literature. In [CITATION_2] , Wang et al. introduce a model of \"perfect recognition\" which treats the gallery as probe data, and computes a set of \"perfect\" similarity scores. A distance from each probe to this model can be computed and used as a feature for a machine learning-based prediction algorithm. This is a minor variation on the features described in [CITATION_3] . Further, for face recognition, Wang et al. use the same eye localization perturbation technique described in [CITATION_4] to take corrective action based on the predictions made.",
